{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Plan-review advisory triage (verdict PASS + signed; 0 blocking). Re-run after remediating the first round (phasing, migration/rollback, callers-affected, file_impact set, What↔AC4 aligned). The second-round advisories, triaged:\n\n- E2/F1 + T9 (where/how the coverage counter is surfaced, its lifecycle): FIXED IN DESIGN. The contract-violation report is surfaced at `verdict[\"coverage\"][\"verification_contract_violations\"]` = `{malformed, duplicates:[idx], unexpected:[idx]}`, computed at decide-time, scoped to the single gate run (no cross-run state), and emitted ONLY when non-empty so the clean-path verdict stays byte-identical (attestation-safe). An ERROR log accompanies it.\n- E1 (Phase 3 `require=` API as a deliverable): ACCEPTED — AC6 verifies the lever behaviorally (a require-mode resolve raises on an unresolved root), which necessarily exercises the new param; the API surface is implied by the test. No separate AC needed.\n- T7 + E1 (Phase 4 \"migration\" — CI docs reference the shell check; old check removal not verified): SCOPE CLARIFIED. Phase 4 does NOT remove the CI shell gate; it ADDS a `compute_over_cap_modules()` function + a structural unit test (belt-and-suspenders). Nothing to migrate/remove, so no doc churn and no removal to verify. AC7 verifies the added structural assertion — correct as written.\n- COH (sequencing vs independent-slice tension): MINOR. Phase 1 gates the PATTERN CHOICE only; each phase still ships as its own mergeable slice. Not contradictory.\n- P6 (DET ac-quality heuristic flags compound 'and' criteria): ACKNOWLEDGED. The DET floor is a structural heuristic; the ACs are individually verifiable as written. Not re-splitting further (over-splitting harms readability) — justified, non-blocking.\n- G5 (epic-scale: 4 phases / 8 ACs): JUSTIFIED as a single story. This is ONE cohesive contract-hardening change (the silent-degrade CLASS) shipped as one reviewable PR; fragmenting into an epic would scatter a single seam-contract design. User directed it as one story to execute now.\n\nNet: no blocking issues; design unchanged except the explicit coverage-key spec above. Proceeding to claim against this signed PASS."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782673876669162001,"uuid":"50a054fb-97ad-47c4-9ae9-88e5fbfb69ba"}